         The Project entails IFC investment in KEP Trust (KEP), the leading microfinance institutions (MFI) in Kosovo, a fragile and conflicted state (FCS) and IDA country, to support expansion of its lending program to domestic individuals, micro and small enterprises (MSEs) including  
         micro agricultural farms and very small agri processing companies. 
          The investment will be provided in Euro for up to three years from IFCs own account and from  
         Global Agricultural and Food Security Program  
         (GAFSP).

